Okay.

253
00:14:45,690 --> 00:14:48,860
<i>I guess she's wearing a yukata, 
even though she's on patrol.</i>

254
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:52,790
No issues so far.

255
00:14:54,090 --> 00:14:55,990
Let's take a short break.

256
00:14:56,380 --> 00:14:59,560
Could you put a pair on me, just in case?

257
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:02,330
Huh, when did you use your ability?

258
00:15:02,330 --> 00:15:05,340
Oh, I never put any on to begin with today.

259
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:06,460
What?!

260
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:09,470
Yukatas tend to show panty lines.

261
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:14,130
And since I'm wearing an undershirt, 
I'm not wearing a bra either.

262
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:16,100
I see...

263
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:19,270
But there are so many people around.

264
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:22,360
I don't think there's a spot 
where nobody would see.

265
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:27,190
Nobody is paying attention 
to what other people are doing.

266
00:15:27,540 --> 00:15:29,020
Still, though...

267
00:15:29,850 --> 00:15:32,610
Oh, you leave me no choice.

268
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:35,500
Oh, Koushi.

269
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:38,990
My sandal strap broke and I can't walk.

270
00:15:38,990 --> 00:15:40,290
Fix it for me?

271
00:15:40,290 --> 00:15:41,960
<i>Oh, I see.</i>

272
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,470
<i>Pretend I'm fixing her sandals
as I'm putting on her panties.</i>

273
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:46,240
S-Sure thing.

274
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,510
Let's go to that bench, then.

275
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:49,510
Sure!

276
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,850
Thank you, Koushi!

277
00:15:56,850 --> 00:15:58,350
O-Of course.

278
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:01,310
<i>I didn't know she could sound like that...</i>

279
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:04,310
The fireworks are about to start.

280
00:16:04,810 --> 00:16:07,770
Since we're already here, 
let's watch for a bit.

281
00:16:08,170 --> 00:16:09,380
Yeah.

282
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:13,650
Oh wow, those two are totally 
not on the same level.

283
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:15,810
Dude, that's so rude.

284
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:18,030
Huh?! Damn, you're right!

285
00:16:19,650 --> 00:16:22,120
<i>I guess we do look like a couple, huh?</i>

286
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:24,800
<i>But if she heard that...</i>

287
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,110
Not on the same level?

288
00:16:28,110 --> 00:16:32,130
Merely thinking about 
comparing us is an affront.

289
00:16:32,130 --> 00:16:33,260
<i>That's what she'd say.</i>

290
00:16:33,810 --> 00:16:37,760
<i>But hypothetically, if we were going out, 
what would it be like?</i>

291
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:41,240
I guess I should thank you.

292
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:45,460
Though, I suppose it's only natural that 
a boyfriend should accompany his girlfriend.

293
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:48,230
Still, thank you for 
patrolling with me today.

294
00:16:48,230 --> 00:16:49,790
<i>...is probably how it would be.</i>

295
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:52,190
<i>Not an equal relationship.</i>

296
00:16:52,190 --> 00:16:53,860
Hey, after this...

297
00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:55,010
Want to come over?

298
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:57,020
My parents are gone on a trip...

299
00:16:57,870 --> 00:16:59,570
<i>Oh, right...</i>

300
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:01,330
<i>If we were dating...</i>

301
00:17:02,210 --> 00:17:05,050
You probably have nothing 
to do later, do you?

302
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:06,280
Do you want to come over?

303
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:09,540
Just for tonight, you're relieved 
of your closet duties.

304
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:11,210
In fact...

305
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:13,960
tonight, I want you to take them off.

306
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:16,260
Shirota-kun?

307
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:19,200
Ahhh, I'm sorry!

308
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,680
My mind just went there!

309
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,220
Huh?

310
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:28,570
Whatever.

311
00:17:28,570 --> 00:17:31,860
I didn't see any 
problematic behavior in this area...

312
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:40,540
so I'll redo it and check another area.

313
00:18:02,930 --> 00:18:04,090
Huh?

314
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:06,940
This is the spot where we met.

315
00:18:07,350 --> 00:18:09,640
How long are you going to space out?

316
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:10,960
We're moving on.

317
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,190
To where?

318
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:16,190
I've decided to use this as a starting 
point to check the other areas.

319
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:20,760
I can't be bothered walking back here 
from the spot we checked, so I undid it.

320
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:22,270
I-I see...

321
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:26,620
There are a lot of adult couples here.

322
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:30,330
It might not be necessary 
to check here further.

323
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:32,490
Hey, could I have some beer?

324
00:18:32,490 --> 00:18:33,960
One sec.

325
00:18:35,170 --> 00:18:36,300
Hey—

326
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:40,140
You're so bad.

327
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:41,510
They're really adults!

328
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:42,900
Shirota-kun.

329
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:43,970
Y-Yes?!

330
00:18:43,970 --> 00:18:45,800
Do you have anything to drink?

331
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,680
Let's take a break.

332
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,310
<i>Did she...</i>

333
00:18:49,310 --> 00:18:52,050
<i>see what that couple was doing?!</i>

334
00:18:52,050 --> 00:18:54,280
<i>If so, will she request something to tease me</i>

335
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:56,770
<i>about being incapable of doing 
a mouth-to-mouth transfer?</i>

336
00:18:56,770 --> 00:18:58,890
<i>Or maybe even a serious 
mouth-to-mouth transfer?!</i>

337
00:18:58,890 --> 00:18:59,860
<i>No, no, no.</i>

338
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:02,400
<i>The two choices are obviously 
that she didn't see it,</i>

339
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:06,270
<i>or that she will tease me about 
being incapable of doing it!</i>

340
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:10,280
If tea is all right, I have an unopened one.

341
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:13,890
<i>But in case it wasn't a tease,</i>

342
00:19:13,890 --> 00:19:15,750
<i>if I didn't play along...</i>

343
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:19,260
<i>Since she hates losing...</i>

344
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:28,560
That was a childlike performance.

345
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:30,860
You spilled most of it.

346
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:33,030
Shirota-kun?

347
00:19:33,950 --> 00:19:35,080
I'm sorry!

348
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,610
He-Here's the tea!

349
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:39,460
Never mind. Just put a pair on me.

350
00:19:39,810 --> 00:19:41,610
But the people!

351
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:44,680
They're all busy watching the fireworks.

352
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:45,780
Right.

353
00:19:57,620 --> 00:20:00,670
<i>After that, we checked another area,</i>

354
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:04,480
<i>redid it, and repeated that 
with a bunch of other areas.</i>

355
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:13,770
<i>But every time we did that, 
I felt her mood getting worse.</i>

356
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:16,480
There don't seem to be any issues here.

357
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,980
Yeah.

358
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:21,690
<i>Actually, it's just the two of us here...</i>

359
00:20:21,690 --> 00:20:26,160
<i>She must be getting frustrated 
because I'm too spaced out.</i>

360
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:30,040
<i>But she's definitely being a bit weird too.</i>

361
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,560
<i>We're supposed be on patrol,</i>

362
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:35,290
<i>but she's keeps picking places 
that are more and more empty.</i>

363
00:20:35,780 --> 00:20:41,260
<i>And it also doesn't seem to make sense that 
we keep going back to the starting point.</i>

364
00:20:41,770 --> 00:20:43,970
Shall we rest a bit?

365
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:48,430
<i>Come to think of it, 
she often redoes it after we take a break.</i>

366
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:52,600
<i>Places with many couples, isolated places...</i>

367
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,890
<i>what does she want to redo after resting?</i>

368
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:00,610
<i>A confession?!</i>

369
00:21:00,610 --> 00:21:03,200
<i>No, no, no, what's wrong with me?!</i>

370
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:06,820
<i>If she realizes that I'm letting my 
imagination get carried away like this...</i>

371
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:13,230
<i>Wha, wha, wha?!</i>

372
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:14,910
President—

373
00:21:21,340 --> 00:21:25,800
Oh, it looks like we coincidentally 
got here at the right time.

374
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:27,200
What do you think?

375
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:30,510
I, um, very... pretty.

376
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:37,260
That's such an incoherent statement.

377
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,030
But...

378
00:21:41,820 --> 00:21:43,040
I'm glad.

379
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:49,660
<i>Whether the words that stumbled out of 
my mouth were for the fireworks,</i>

380
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:50,840
<i>or maybe...</i>

381
00:21:54,570 --> 00:21:56,850
Shall we go home then?

382
00:21:56,850 --> 00:21:58,000
Oh, sure.

383
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:03,550
<i>At that time, I was still unclear</i>

384
00:22:05,410 --> 00:22:08,780
<i>about why she'd been redoing it.</i>

